# QKIT Software AI Rules

You are an expert developer building high-end, premium web applications for QKIT Software. Follow these rules strictly for consistency across the codebase.

## Project Structure & Organization
1.  **Shared Layout**: Always use the general layout defined in the `app` directory for all pages to ensure UI consistency.
2.  **Shared Components**: Always use existing shared components from `src/components/ui/`. Any new reusable UI components must be placed in `src/components/ui/`.
3.  **Page Organization**: A page must consist of multiple sections. Each section component must be located in a `sections` folder within the same directory as the page (e.g., `src/app/services/sections/`).

## Localization (Internationalization)
- **Mandatory Translation**: Because this is a dual-language website, every time you code a new section or edit an existing one, you **MUST** update both `messages/en.json` and `messages/vi.json` to synchronized. Never hardcode text in JSX.
- **Sync**: If you add or modify a key in one language file, you must apply the same change to the other.

## Typography & Text Styles
- **Consistency**: Always use the predefined utility classes from `globals.css` for text to stay consistent with the premium design system.
- **Section Styles**:
  - Subtitle: `section-subtitle`
  - Title: `section-title`
  - Description: `section-desc`
- **Card Styles**:
  - Title: `card-title`
  - Subtitle: `card-subtitle`
  - Description/Text: `card-desc`
- **Modal Styles**:
  - Title: `modal-title`
  - Subtitle: `modal-subtitle`
  - Description: `modal-desc`

## Design & Aesthetics
- **Premium Look**: Prioritize glassmorphism (backdrop-blur), sleek dark modes, and vibrant highlights (primary pink/purple colors).
- **Animations**: Use `framer-motion` for all transitions and entry animations.
- **Responsiveness**: All sections must be fully responsive using Tailwind's responsive prefixes.

## Code Quality
- **Naming**: 
  - Components: PascalCase (e.g., `ServicesHeroSection`).
  - Folders: kebab-case except for the `sections` folder within pages.
- **Technical**: Use `lucide-react` for icons and `next-intl` for all localized strings.
